'''Tempo Reale''' is an electronic music research, production, and educational centre, based in [[Florence]], Italy. It was founded by composer [[Luciano Berio]], who served as the centre's director from 1987 to 2000, and as honorary president until his death in 2003.<ref name=intro>{{cite web |url=http://www.temporeale.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=58&Itemid=88&lang=en |title=A colloquio con Luciano Berio &#124; Tempo Reale |publisher=Temporeale.it |date= |accessdate=2012-08-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127083346/http://www.temporeale.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=58&Itemid=88&lang=en |archivedate=2013-01-27 |df= }}</ref> The centre has celebrated its 25-year anniversary in 2012.<ref name=intro/><ref name=obit>{{cite news|author= |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1431261/Luciano-Berio.html |title=Luciano Berio |publisher=Telegraph |date=2003-05-28 |accessdate=2012-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.temporeale.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=443&Itemid=197&lang=en |title=Tempo Reale Collection &#124; Tempo Reale |publisher=Temporeale.it |date= |accessdate=2012-08-20}}</ref>
== Notable collaborators with Luciano Berio == * [[Giorgio Battistelli]] (Italian composer) * [[Henri Pousseur]] (Belgian composer) * [[David Moss (musician)|David Moss]] (American composer and percussionist, founder a director of ''Institute for Living Voice'' in [[Antwerp]]) * [[Renzo Piano]]{{citation needed|date=August 2012}}
